headline: Trump's Fed chair race continues: Kevin Hassett vs. Kevin Warsh
summary: President Trump will be announcing his pick for the next Federal Reserve chairman in the coming days, replacing current Fed Chair Jerome Powell when his term ends in 2026. National Economic Council director Kevin Hassett and former Fed Governor Kevin Warsh are widely considered to be the frontrunners of Trump's alleged shortlist. Yahoo Finance Fed Correspondent Jennifer Schonberger joins Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton to outline what we know right now about the battle of the Kevins. Make sure to check out Jennifer Schonberger's profiles of the other three shortlist candidates: Fed Governor Chris Waller, Fed Vice Chair of Supervision Michelle Bowman, and BlackRock's (BLK) head of fixed income Rick Rieder. For even more, you can take a look at Jen's interview with Hassett and Yahoo Finance anchor Julie Hyman's interview with Rieder. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Stock Bulls Have a Worryingly Long List of 2026 Risks to Ponder
summary: A lot is riding on artificial intelligence winners proving that, rather than forming a bubble, they have further to climb.  “AI is set to transform industries and investment opportunities, but it also brings the risk of overenthusiasm,” said Kristin Lemkau, chief executive officer of JPMorgan Wealth Management.  “Fragmentation, where the global order is dividing into competing blocs and supply chains, means that resilience and security are more important than ever,” Lemkau said.
